description:
The Kult series introduces this setting anew with parole officer Tomas Zenk, one of the few who can pierce the illusion. As he overcomes monsters sent to kill him, Zenk discovers the true extent of his powers, including the ability to exert control over the machinery of humanity's enslavement. But will he aid the forces attempting to bring down the illusion . . . or succumb to the temptations of power?

Collected in Kult.
name: Kult

description:
Frank Castle's crusade on crime continues, this time helmed by Greg Rucka!

Continued from the events of Franken-Castle and the Punisher: In the Blood mini-series. Fifth regular ongoing launched as part of Marvel's Big Shots Initiative, a promotion in which three A-list writers were paired with three characters who could use the attention. Greg Rucka's Punisher, with Marco Checchetto on art, debuted along with Mark Waid's Daredevil and Brian Michael Bendis' Moon Knight. After issue 16, the series is continued in a new mini-series named Punisher: War Zone.

Collected Editions

  • Punisher by Greg Rucka Vol. 1 (#1-5 and material from Spider-Island: I Love New York City)
  • Punisher by Greg Rucka Vol. 2 (#6-10, Daredevil #11 and Avenging Spider-Man #6)
  • Daredevil by Mark Waid Omnibus Volume 1 (#10)
  • Punisher by Greg Rucka Vol. 3 (#11-16)
name: The Punisher
